# Emechetian Resources

# Metadata Schema v1.0

This document defines the metadata standard adopted by the Emechetian Resources Project. The schema is designed to support automatic harvesting from bibliographic databases while allowing future human curation when necessary.

---

# 1. Identification

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| id | Unique identifier assigned by Emechetian Resources (e.g., ER000001). |
| review_status | Record status (pending, validated, excluded). |
| record_source | How the record entered the database (automatic, manual, imported). |
| metadata_reliability | Confidence level of the harvested metadata (high, medium, low). |

---

# 2. Bibliographic Information

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| publication_type | journal_article, masters_thesis, doctoral_thesis, etc. |
| title | Full title of the publication. |
| authors | Author(s). |
| journal_or_institution | Journal or degree-granting institution. |
| country | Country of the institution. |
| language | Language of publication. |
| year | Publication year. |
| doi | Digital Object Identifier. |
| url | Permanent URL. |

---

# 3. Research Content

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| abstract | Publication abstract. |
| keywords | Original keywords provided by the publication. |
| emecheta_work_analyzed | One or more works by Buchi Emecheta discussed in the publication. |
| themes | Controlled vocabulary assigned by Emechetian Resources. |
| theoretical_framework | Main theoretical framework(s). |
| methodology | Research methodology. |
| main_findings | Main conclusions of the study. |

---

# 4. Discovery & Access

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| citation_count | Number of citations (when available). |
| source_databases | Databases where the record was found (OpenAlex, Crossref, Scopus, etc.). |
| open_access | yes, no, or unknown. |

---

# 5. Internal Management

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| date_added | Date the record entered the database. |
| last_updated | Date of the latest metadata update. |
| notes | Internal notes for project maintenance. |

---

# General Principles

- All metadata field names are maintained in English.
- Multiple values within the same field are separated by semicolons (;).
- Whenever possible, metadata is harvested automatically from trusted sources.
- Human curation is optional and intended only to enrich records with literary-specific information not available in bibliographic databases.
- Missing information should remain blank rather than inferred.
